-- Mauritius New Vehicles Rise 30% in Quarter, l’Express Reports
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-05-03T09:39:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/mauritius-new-vehicles-rise-30-in-quarter-l-express-reports.html
Sales of new vehicles in Mauritius
rose 30 percent to 2,400 in the first quarter through March, the
Port Louis-based l’Express newspaper reported, citing Gilles
Lalanne, chairman of the country’s Motor Vehicles Dealers
Association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
